revision.text:
{{nihongo|'''Tarumaezan Shrine'''|樽前山神社}} is a [[Shinto shrine]] in [[Tomakomai]], [[Iburi Subprefecture]], [[Hokkaidō]], [[Japan]]. It is located on [[Mount Tarumae]].
==See also== * [[List of Shinto shrines in Japan#Hokkaid.C5.8D|List of Shinto shrines in Hokkaidō]]
==External links== *[https://www.tarumaesanjinja.net Official website]
{{Shinto shrine}}
[[Category:Shinto shrines in Hokkaido]]
{{Japan-religious-struct-stub}}

{{nihongo|'''Tarumaezan Shrine'''|樽前山神社}} is a [[Shinto shrine]] in [[Tomakomai]], [[Iburi Subprefecture]], [[Hokkaidō]], [[Japan]]. It is located on [[Mount Tarumae]], and it was promoted to a prefectural shrine in 1936. It enshrines the Shinto [[kami]] Kukunochi, Kaya no hime, and Oyamatsumi.
==See also== * [[List of Shinto shrines in Japan#Hokkaid.C5.8D|List of Shinto shrines in Hokkaidō]]
==External links== *[https://www.tarumaesanjinja.net Official website]
